Let's create a new site using the janusweb framework. Use Janus' JML markup in an HTML page to define a new room. We'll start off with this basic markup:

<html>
<body>
<script src="https://web.janusxr.org/1.5.53/janusweb.js"></script>
<janus-viewer>
<assets>
</assets>
<room>
</room>
</janus-viewer>
</body>
</html>

We'll define some custom elements, for the <airhockey-table>, <airhockey-paddle>, <airhockey-puck>, and <airhockey-scoreboard>. We'll also need an <airhockey-goal> object to represent each player's goal. The airhockey-table will have a goal at each end, and the scoreboard will reflect any time the puck collides with the respective player's goal.

Custom elements are defined with this syntax:

janus.registerElement('airhockey-table', {
  someattribute: "default string value",
  numericattribute: 1.2,
  booleanattribute: true,

  create() {
    // create any child objects with this.createObject('object', { id: 'primitivename', pos: "x y z", scale: "xscale yscale zscale", col: "colorname or #hexcode" })
  },
  update(dt) {
    // called once per frame
  }
});

